<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870311-0116 </DOCNO><HL> Procter andamp; Gamble PicksAd Agency for 2 Products</HL><DD> 03/11/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> PG </IN><DATELINE> CINCINNATI  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Procter andamp; Gamble Co. said it appointed Slater, Hanft, Martin Inc. as its advertising agency for Dramamine and Icy Hot.    Pandamp;G acquired Dramamine, a motion sickness treatment, and Icy Hot, a pain-relieving ointment, from G.D. Searle andamp; Co. in November 1985. The consumer products concern said that since the acquisition, the products haven't been assigned to specific agencies.    In addition to Dramamine and Icy Hot, New York-based Slater Hanft handles Pandamp;G's Percogesic, an aspirin-free pain reliever. </TEXT></DOC>